    Additionally, users weren‚Äôt so anxious about their wine picks that they would think to download an app to present better wine picks. Although a mobile app might solve for anxieties and produce desired outcomes, user acquisition would most likely be prohibitively expensive
    Prototype #2: Virtual Reality
